00:29:59,646 --> 00:30:02,979
MARK:
I like an indoor pool. Year-round usage.

480
00:30:03,216 --> 00:30:06,845
I like the steam off it in the winter.
Very mysterious, that steam.

481
00:30:07,020 --> 00:30:08,510
Well, Marty...

482
00:30:10,123 --> 00:30:13,058
...when you started work at ADM,
how much money did you want?

483
00:30:13,326 --> 00:30:14,623
I wanted 50 grand.

484
00:30:15,662 --> 00:30:19,928
But I went and told Terry,
"We can't get this guy for less than 75."

485
00:30:20,100 --> 00:30:22,568
- Yeah.
- I got it for you. You were the first I hired.

486
00:30:22,736 --> 00:30:25,864
You've always been really generous
with me. And I appreciate it.

487
00:30:26,039 --> 00:30:28,064
Here's what I want you to do.

488
00:30:28,742 --> 00:30:30,972
I want you to write down a name.

489
00:30:32,412 --> 00:30:36,007
Okay. What's the name?

490
00:30:37,417 --> 00:30:39,851
Nordkron Chemie.

491
00:30:40,587 --> 00:30:45,081
What is that, like,
a Nigerian name or something?

492
00:30:45,258 --> 00:30:48,591
I like my hands. I think they're probably
my favorite part of my body.

493
00:30:48,762 --> 00:30:51,629
I think that can be used to my advantage
in social situations.

494
00:30:51,798 --> 00:30:55,393
If I can get people focused on my hands,
I can get a good result in a meeting.

495
00:30:55,569 --> 00:30:57,230
Eye contact is real important too.

496
00:30:57,404 --> 00:30:59,531
Hey, I'm gonna check messages.

497
00:31:02,209 --> 00:31:04,200
[CHATTERING INDISTINCTLY]

498
00:31:08,415 --> 00:31:10,849
AUTOMATED MALE VOICE:
You have one message.

499
00:31:11,585 --> 00:31:13,576
[PAGER BEEPING OVER PHONE]

500
00:31:14,855 --> 00:31:16,846
My phone died. I was on with the plant.

501
00:31:17,023 --> 00:31:19,184
Is there a payphone,
a public but kind of...?

502
00:31:19,359 --> 00:31:20,519
- Across the lobby.
- Right.

503
00:31:20,694 --> 00:31:23,458
- Mark, this is important bioproduct stuff.
- I know.

504
00:31:23,630 --> 00:31:25,063
Hi, Dave. How's Holly doing?

505
00:31:25,232 --> 00:31:26,392
DAVE: She's good.
- Great.

506
00:31:26,566 --> 00:31:27,794
It's the plant.

507
00:31:27,968 --> 00:31:30,459
SHEPARD [OVER PHONE]: FBI.
- Brian, it's Mark.

508
00:31:30,637 --> 00:31:33,299
I told you, I'm out of town
on business this week.

509
00:31:33,473 --> 00:31:35,839
The case is getting some attention
from the Bureau.

510
00:31:36,009 --> 00:31:37,772
There's another agent working
with me.

511
00:31:37,944 --> 00:31:39,809
MARK: I can't talk right now.
I have a meeting.

512
00:31:39,980 --> 00:31:42,278
I have people waiting for me. Bye.

513
00:31:43,483 --> 00:31:45,075
I'm here, Dave.

514
00:31:45,819 --> 00:31:49,152
Being able to do two things at once
is a big part of success.

515
00:31:49,322 --> 00:31:51,688
I try and do abdominal exercises...
Isometrics.

516
00:31:51,858 --> 00:31:53,348
- Even when I'm at a meeting.

517
00:31:53,527 --> 00:31:55,392
Tensing. Holding.

518
00:31:55,562 --> 00:31:56,654
Then releasing.

519
00:31:56,930 --> 00:31:59,831
I'll floss in the shower
while the conditioner is in my hair...

520
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:01,991
...when you're just supposed
to leave it in.

521
00:32:02,169 --> 00:32:05,229
Those things can really add up
to a significant time savings.

522
00:32:05,405 --> 00:32:06,838
Hey, Kirk.

523
00:32:07,440 --> 00:32:08,737
I'll be heading to Europe...

524
00:32:08,909 --> 00:32:12,743
...and I thought I could just hand deliver
that check for the ABP deal in person.

525
00:32:12,913 --> 00:32:14,437
Remind me. ABP deal?

526
00:32:14,681 --> 00:32:17,809
It's a threonine microbe.
They're making substantial improvements.

527
00:32:17,984 --> 00:32:20,316
We want to get into the market.
That's the invoice.

528
00:32:20,487 --> 00:32:21,579
We'll just overnight it.

529
00:32:21,755 --> 00:32:24,918
I'm gonna see this Thorstensson guy,
so I'll just hand it to him.

530
00:32:29,229 --> 00:32:31,697
The metric system never panned out.
We had rulers...

531
00:32:31,865 --> 00:32:34,299
...with inches on one edge,
centimeters on the other.

532
00:32:34,467 --> 00:32:38,130
I pronounced it "centimeters" instead of
"centimeters" and nobody corrected me.

533
00:32:38,305 --> 00:32:41,536
They let me walk around stupid.
I'm not upset we never crossed over...

534
00:32:41,708 --> 00:32:43,903
...though it's helpful
to know the conversions.

535
00:32:44,077 --> 00:32:46,272
The liter bottle is the thing
that caught on...

536
00:32:46,446 --> 00:32:49,472
...because it's a nicer word,
"liter" than "quart."

537
00:32:49,649 --> 00:32:50,946
Quart.

538
00:32:51,117 --> 00:32:52,379
Quart.

539
00:32:53,053 --> 00:32:54,782
MARTY:
Mark, it's Marty calling again.

540
00:32:55,522 --> 00:32:56,784
[PHONE BEEPS]

541
00:32:56,957 --> 00:32:58,356
AUTOMATED VOICE:
Message deleted.

542
00:32:58,525 --> 00:32:59,890
[PAGER BEEPING OVER PHONE]

543
00:33:00,060 --> 00:33:01,425
[PHONE BEEPS]

544
00:33:04,497 --> 00:33:06,522
[RINGS]

545
00:33:10,170 --> 00:33:11,797
FBI, Agent Shepard.

546
00:33:11,972 --> 00:33:13,735
Brian, it's Mark.

547
00:33:14,007 --> 00:33:16,339
Look, it's been hard for me
to return a page...

548
00:33:16,509 --> 00:33:18,943
...as I am out of the country
at the moment.

549
00:33:19,446 --> 00:33:22,847
Listen, we need to know if you've had
any further contact with Nakawara.

550
00:33:23,016 --> 00:33:26,179
I told you already
that the guy stopped calling.

551
00:33:26,353 --> 00:33:30,687
Well, what about the price fixing? Have
you been able to make any more tapes?

552
00:33:30,857 --> 00:33:33,826
I think you guys hanging around
has everybody scared straight.

553
00:33:33,994 --> 00:33:36,326
The word is we're doing everything
by the book now.

554
00:33:36,496 --> 00:33:39,021
Mick said it's over. No more price fixing.

555
00:33:39,199 --> 00:33:43,101
What? When did this happen,
this conversation?

556
00:33:43,270 --> 00:33:48,173
Everything has changed. I got lysine up
and running. The virus is gone.

557
00:33:48,341 --> 00:33:51,469
Mick brought me into his office,
he sat me down.

558
00:33:51,645 --> 00:33:54,910
He said, "Whitacre, from now on
we're doing things your way."

559
00:33:55,081 --> 00:33:56,708
Mark.

560
00:33:56,883 --> 00:34:00,375
Look, Mark,
the FBI knows about the crimes.

561
00:34:00,553 --> 00:34:03,044
We're gonna investigate either way.

562
00:34:03,223 --> 00:34:05,088
Either way?
What does "either way" mean?

563
00:34:05,258 --> 00:34:07,158
We really need to get together.

564
00:34:07,327 --> 00:34:10,763
It is a different approach there now.
I'm telling you, it's all...

565
00:34:10,931 --> 00:34:13,195
Everything's changed.

566
00:34:13,366 --> 00:34:16,858
My plane is boarding. I gotta go.
I gotta go.

567
00:34:17,671 --> 00:34:19,104
Ah!

568
00:34:28,682 --> 00:34:31,446
- Everything okay?
- Yeah, fine.

569
00:34:31,618 --> 00:34:32,915
Kids.

570
00:34:33,153 --> 00:34:36,589
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

571
00:34:37,023 --> 00:34:39,514
- Where were we?
- We were discussing bonuses.

572
00:34:40,193 --> 00:34:42,627
And we should be discussing Ferraris.

573
00:34:43,129 --> 00:34:44,892
[SPEAKING IN GERMAN]

574
00:34:45,865 --> 00:34:49,301
You have Fullfederhaltertinte
all over your shirt.

575
00:34:49,970 --> 00:34:51,733
Ow.

576
00:34:51,938 --> 00:34:53,906
One of the Japanese guys
told me a story.

577
00:34:54,074 --> 00:34:55,905
This lysine salesman is in a meeting...

578
00:34:56,076 --> 00:34:58,704
...with someone from ConAgra
or some other company.

579
00:34:58,878 --> 00:35:01,244
And the client leans forward and says:

580
00:35:01,414 --> 00:35:05,407
"I have the same tie as you,
only the pattern is reversed."

581
00:35:05,852 --> 00:35:09,049
And then he drops dead,
face down on the table.

582
00:35:09,222 --> 00:35:12,020
Alive and then dead.

583
00:35:12,192 --> 00:35:13,489
Brain aneurysm.

584
00:35:14,327 --> 00:35:17,763
Maybe everyone has a sentence like that,
a little time bomb.

585
00:35:17,931 --> 00:35:21,697
"I have the same tie as you,
only the pattern's reversed."

586
00:35:21,868 --> 00:35:25,895
Dead. The last thing they'll ever say.
Something like...

587
00:35:26,072 --> 00:35:29,303
High-fructose corn syrup.
There it is again.

588
00:35:29,476 --> 00:35:32,570
SHEPARD: He said that Andreas called
him into a marketing meeting.

589
00:35:32,746 --> 00:35:34,509
He might be late.

590
00:35:34,948 --> 00:35:38,384
If he doesn't show, the government
ought to charge him for the room.

591
00:35:38,685 --> 00:35:40,846
[PHONE RINGS]

592
00:35:41,021 --> 00:35:43,114
And here it comes.

593
00:35:47,594 --> 00:35:48,856
Shepard.

594
00:35:49,029 --> 00:35:52,487
MARK: I can't come to the hotel tonight.
I'm still at work.

595
00:35:52,665 --> 00:35:54,257
SHEPARD:
Mark, this is the third time.

596
00:35:54,434 --> 00:35:56,925
MARK:
I gotta go. I have work to do.

597
00:35:57,437 --> 00:36:01,771
- Mark, you can't keep canceling.
- Look, I can't live two lives.

598
00:36:01,941 --> 00:36:05,536
They just offered me a $ 100,000 raise,
okay?

599
00:36:05,712 --> 00:36:08,112
I'm not gonna lose my job
because of you guys.

600
00:36:08,281 --> 00:36:11,045
I have a family.
I'm building stables across the road.

601
00:36:11,217 --> 00:36:15,381
- But you told us...
- The price fixing is over. It's over.

602
00:36:15,555 --> 00:36:18,752
Hey, Mick.
I'm getting off the phone now.

603
00:36:18,925 --> 00:36:20,893
Mark, listen to me.

604
00:36:21,061 --> 00:36:24,929
The only logical thing for you to do
is cooperate.

605
00:36:25,565 --> 00:36:26,657
What happens if I don't?

606
00:36:26,833 --> 00:36:30,963
Then somebody else will,
and you'll end up being a defendant.

607
00:36:31,137 --> 00:36:34,800
The tapes don't say anything,
because it's over. Mick said.

608
00:36:34,974 --> 00:36:36,566
We have a whole new policy.

609
00:36:36,743 --> 00:36:42,113
Fine, if that's what he said. Then I want
to hear the tape. We need tapes, Mark.

610
00:36:43,483 --> 00:36:45,713
Okay, I never made any tapes.

611
00:36:45,885 --> 00:36:49,252
I never made any because there's not
gonna be anything on the tapes.

612
00:36:49,422 --> 00:36:51,413
It's over, and they'd just be stupid tapes.

613
00:36:51,591 --> 00:36:53,024
- Mark, come on.
- Look, how...?

614
00:36:53,193 --> 00:36:55,923
You tell me how I can prove it to you,
and I will.

615
00:37:16,316 --> 00:37:18,307
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

616
00:37:39,405 --> 00:37:42,374
Mick Andreas and his dad
would never lie for me.

617
00:37:42,542 --> 00:37:44,874
They say we're in it together.
What a joke.

618
00:37:45,044 --> 00:37:47,979
Team-building offsite meetings
at some lake in Wisconsin.

619
00:37:48,148 --> 00:37:50,673
I can't protect these guys
if they're breaking the law.

620
00:37:50,850 --> 00:37:53,546
Hey, I tried.
Anybody could see the choices I had.

621
00:37:53,720 --> 00:37:56,348
I did my best for ADM.
You don't see them here in the chair.

622
00:37:56,523 --> 00:37:58,184
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

623
00:37:58,658 --> 00:38:00,819
Hey, how'd I do?

624
00:38:00,994 --> 00:38:02,791
SHEPARD:
Mark, we have some problems.

625
00:38:02,962 --> 00:38:07,524
Wait a minute. I was looking at the thing.
The needle didn't even move.

626
00:38:07,700 --> 00:38:10,965
Mark, you don't know
how to read a polygraph.

627
00:38:11,137 --> 00:38:13,799
Well, first of all,
they're not 100 percent accurate.

628
00:38:13,973 --> 00:38:16,168
Mark, you splattered the walls with ink.

629
00:38:16,676 --> 00:38:20,442
Come on. Extortionists just don't leave
their name and number, then go away.

630
00:38:20,613 --> 00:38:22,012
SHEPARD:
I know it's tough...

631
00:38:22,448 --> 00:38:25,906
...keeping it all bottled up inside,
keeping it a secret.

632
00:38:26,452 --> 00:38:30,183
But there's only one good choice for you.
That's all there's ever been.

633
00:38:30,857 --> 00:38:33,155
There's something
you're not telling us...

634
00:38:33,326 --> 00:38:39,196
...but the only way to protect yourself
is to be completely honest.

635
00:38:47,040 --> 00:38:48,632
MARK:
Okay.

636
00:38:49,876 --> 00:38:51,366
Okay.

637
00:38:53,746 --> 00:38:54,770
[SIGHS]

638
00:38:54,948 --> 00:38:56,848
You realize...

639
00:38:58,585 --> 00:39:01,452
...that this can all be used against you
in a court of law.

640
00:39:01,621 --> 00:39:04,681
I'll have to write it all up,
and you'll have to sign it.

641
00:39:04,857 --> 00:39:07,052
We're going to find out what's going on,
Mark.

642
00:39:07,927 --> 00:39:10,828
You're not leaving this room
until you tell us what's going on.

643
00:39:10,997 --> 00:39:13,363
SHEPARD: So before you answer
any more questions...

644
00:39:13,533 --> 00:39:15,626
...I want you to think about Ginger...

645
00:39:15,802 --> 00:39:18,202
...and your family, and your career.

646
00:39:21,040 --> 00:39:23,565
HERNDON:
What happened with Nakawara?

647
00:39:24,143 --> 00:39:25,701
Is there a mole?

648
00:39:29,082 --> 00:39:34,384
Well, yeah, I think there has definitely
been a mole, before, at ADM.

649
00:39:41,928 --> 00:39:43,589
- I made it up.
- Jesus, Mark.

650
00:39:43,763 --> 00:39:44,991
MARK:
I had to.

651
00:39:45,164 --> 00:39:48,361
Look, we've had problems with viruses
at the plant...

652
00:39:48,534 --> 00:39:50,900
...and we're way behind our projections.

653
00:39:51,070 --> 00:39:54,699
Dwayne is thinking about shutting us down
and everybody's looking to me.

654
00:39:54,874 --> 00:39:57,934
It's all "Blame it on Whitacre."
That's how it is over there.

655
00:39:58,111 --> 00:40:00,341
We're talking about my job here.

656
00:40:00,513 --> 00:40:05,109
I came all the way over from Europe,
relocated my family. They made me a VP.

657
00:40:05,652 --> 00:40:09,281
Uh... Uh... What about the price fixing?
It isn't over, is it?

658
00:40:09,455 --> 00:40:11,286
I mean, there's no new attitude, right?

659
00:40:11,457 --> 00:40:15,291
It's been going on as recently
as three weeks ago. Nothing's changed.

660
00:40:15,461 --> 00:40:18,692
It's not just lysine. It's citric,
it's gluconate...

661
00:40:18,865 --> 00:40:21,993
A guy left the company because
he wouldn't do it. He was forced out.

662
00:40:22,168 --> 00:40:24,227
The gluconate guy, he's out of a job.

663
00:40:24,404 --> 00:40:27,999
I met with the guys from Ajinomoto
just last month in Chicago.

664
00:40:28,174 --> 00:40:32,440
The whole point
was to actually set volume levels.

665
00:40:32,612 --> 00:40:35,513
You set the volume levels,
determine what the market is...

666
00:40:35,682 --> 00:40:39,675
...and then you figure out workable prices.
We got another meeting next month.

667
00:40:41,154 --> 00:40:43,884
If there's anything else you want to add,
now is the time.

668
00:40:44,057 --> 00:40:46,025
What else is there?

669
00:40:56,169 --> 00:40:59,661
Seven-thirty a.m., March 17th...

670
00:40:59,839 --> 00:41:01,500
...1993.

671
00:41:01,708 --> 00:41:06,975
I have parked the car. I am approaching
the entrance to the office.

672
00:41:08,514 --> 00:41:10,505
Entrance breached.

673
00:41:11,017 --> 00:41:15,147
Terrance Wilson.
President of our corn businesses.

674
00:41:15,455 --> 00:41:18,583
Did our friend from Japan
call last night?

675
00:41:18,758 --> 00:41:20,316
No, he wasn't in.

676
00:41:20,493 --> 00:41:24,020
MARK: Well, I spoke with Mimoto
and he is pissed.

677
00:41:24,197 --> 00:41:26,688
He says there will be no peace
in lysine...

678
00:41:26,866 --> 00:41:29,926
...until we bring production down
to the levels we promised.

679
00:41:30,103 --> 00:41:34,631
Well, in '92, we did exactly what we
told him we would do in terms of volume.

680
00:41:34,807 --> 00:41:37,571
Exactly. Now, no promise.

681
00:41:37,744 --> 00:41:39,211
He says he wants to talk to you.

682
00:41:39,379 --> 00:41:44,646
Yeah? Well, I'll be right there saying:
"Listen here, you mousy motherfucker."

683
00:41:47,553 --> 00:41:51,990
That was Terry Wilson talking
about setting volume...

684
00:41:52,158 --> 00:41:55,889
...and price levels
with our Japanese competitor...

685
00:41:56,062 --> 00:41:58,462
...Ajinomoto Corporation.

686
00:41:59,132 --> 00:42:01,828
By the way, there was no discussion
with Mimoto last night.

687
00:42:02,001 --> 00:42:04,469
I did that for illustration purposes only.

688
00:42:04,637 --> 00:42:06,935
I repeat, no discussion with Mimoto.

689
00:42:07,106 --> 00:42:11,008
LIZ: Morning, Mark.
- Good morning, Liz Taylor, secretary.

690
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:21,744
[SPEAKS IN JAPANESE]

691
00:42:21,921 --> 00:42:23,889
- Please, come in.
- Hello. Good morning.

692
00:42:24,056 --> 00:42:27,583
Good morning. Hello. Good morning.
Good morning.

693
00:42:28,261 --> 00:42:30,525
Before we even deal
with Latin America...

694
00:42:30,696 --> 00:42:34,598
...we have to agree
that we are gonna swap numbers.

695
00:42:34,767 --> 00:42:36,530
It's the only way this is gonna work.

696
00:42:36,702 --> 00:42:41,605
Keep everybody on target.
It's possible to do. Got to be very careful.

697
00:42:42,041 --> 00:42:44,407
Need to check your phones.

698
00:42:45,611 --> 00:42:49,911
Excuse me, I need a comfort break.
Pardon me.

699
00:42:58,691 --> 00:43:00,716
Side two, tape one.

700
00:43:00,893 --> 00:43:03,760
Side two, tape one.

701
00:43:04,630 --> 00:43:07,531
I've got well over two million
frequent flyer miles.

702
00:43:07,700 --> 00:43:09,634
I'm pretty much platinum
across the board.

703
00:43:09,802 --> 00:43:12,236
I get a letter from the CEO every year,
thanking me.

704
00:43:12,405 --> 00:43:14,669
It's a form letter.
It looks like he's signing it.

705
00:43:14,841 --> 00:43:18,368
They probably walk in and he signs
like a hundred while he's on the phone.

706
00:43:20,947 --> 00:43:25,043
Oh, it went great. I think we're gonna
be able to keep it at a buck and a quarter.

707
00:43:25,218 --> 00:43:26,617
[SNEEZES]

708
00:43:27,987 --> 00:43:32,253
Now what happens? Something you
breathe in on an airplane, some bacteria...

709
00:43:32,425 --> 00:43:34,689
...and now it's in his hands, the cup,
the phone.

710
00:43:34,861 --> 00:43:38,058
Probably got it from his kids
and now I'll spend the weekend with it.

711
00:43:38,231 --> 00:43:41,598
I'll miss a few days or Alexander will
