00:57:12,006 --> 00:57:15,100
The corporate culture's
gonna change a little bit for you.

945
00:57:15,276 --> 00:57:17,176
MARK:
I should say so.

946
00:57:17,345 --> 00:57:20,007
- Yeah.
- We should just focus on the raid.

947
00:57:20,181 --> 00:57:21,205
- Right?
- Yes.

948
00:58:04,125 --> 00:58:08,494
- Mark, you're making that up.
- No, Archer, the A in ADM...

949
00:58:08,663 --> 00:58:12,326
...choked to death, 1947,
on a chicken bone.

950
00:58:12,500 --> 00:58:14,468
Fact. Fact.

951
00:58:14,636 --> 00:58:17,628
Well, there you have it,
from Mark Whitacre, Ph.D.

952
00:58:17,906 --> 00:58:21,273
You know what the Ph.D. Stands for,
don't you? Piled Higher and Deeper.

953
00:58:21,442 --> 00:58:26,141
Heh. Let me guess. Daniels was killed
by a pig and the cows got Midland.

954
00:58:26,314 --> 00:58:30,774
[ALL LAUGH]

955
00:58:30,985 --> 00:58:33,453
A chicken got Archer.
I'll tell you, 50 years later...

956
00:58:33,621 --> 00:58:36,522
...our deals with Tyson Farms,
Foster Farms...

957
00:58:36,691 --> 00:58:38,158
...what's the body count?

958
00:58:38,326 --> 00:58:42,888
Mr. Wilson, Mr. Whitacre,
I'm Bob Herndon and I'm an FBI agent.

959
00:58:43,064 --> 00:58:45,498
- This is Special Agent Shepard.
- What is going on?

960
00:58:45,667 --> 00:58:48,397
- Mr. Whitacre, would you come with me?
MARK: I don't...

961
00:58:48,569 --> 00:58:51,800
- I have no idea what this is about.
- Mr. Whitacre, please.

962
00:58:51,973 --> 00:58:54,066
- Could you come with us?
- Do I need a lawyer?

963
00:58:54,242 --> 00:58:56,335
MARK: A lawyer? Terry.
- Excuse me.

964
00:58:56,844 --> 00:58:59,335
I saved a guy once at a restaurant
in Hong Kong.

965
00:58:59,614 --> 00:59:03,015
He was choking and I got him
to throw himself over the back of his chair.

966
00:59:03,184 --> 00:59:06,517
He sends me cards on holidays
just to say thanks.

967
00:59:06,788 --> 00:59:09,279
Tells me what his kids are studying.
He remembers me.

968
00:59:09,524 --> 00:59:12,493
You can take first-aid courses
from your local fire department.

969
00:59:12,660 --> 00:59:16,357
You got a reason for embarrassing my
colleague and I in front of a prospect?

970
00:59:16,531 --> 00:59:18,226
This is a serious matter.

971
00:59:18,399 --> 00:59:22,028
It involves an international investigation
into price fixing.

972
00:59:22,370 --> 00:59:25,134
We have seen you and your boss,
Mick Andreas...

973
00:59:25,373 --> 00:59:27,933
...conspire with your competitors
to fix prices.

974
00:59:28,109 --> 00:59:30,634
We have seen you tell others to do it.

975
00:59:30,812 --> 00:59:32,245
There will be indictments.

976
00:59:32,413 --> 00:59:34,574
Search warrants have been issued.

977
00:59:34,749 --> 00:59:39,948
And some people, people who you know
and work with, will be going to jail.

978
00:59:41,055 --> 00:59:42,613
MARK:
Look at that.

979
00:59:42,790 --> 00:59:46,157
Look at that.
Look at Terry and Bob.

980
00:59:46,327 --> 00:59:49,490
Oh, I wish I could be a fly on that wall.

981
00:59:49,731 --> 00:59:52,666
Oh, hey, I was good, right?
Didn't I seem really scared?

982
00:59:52,834 --> 00:59:54,324
I actually felt scared.

983
00:59:54,502 --> 00:59:56,561
Remember what we told you, all right?

984
00:59:56,738 --> 00:59:59,002
Tell them you're that cooperating
first thing...

985
00:59:59,173 --> 01:00:02,609
...and do not take one of their lawyers.
- Right. No.

986
01:00:02,777 --> 01:00:03,971
MARK:
What'd you say to your guy?

987
01:00:04,145 --> 01:00:05,976
WILSON:
Nothing, I told him nothing. Slow down.

988
01:00:06,147 --> 01:00:07,444
MARK:
Me neither. I said nothing.

989
01:00:07,615 --> 01:00:10,516
WILSON: He said that he had price-fixing
tapes. What the fuck is that?

990
01:00:10,685 --> 01:00:14,553
MARK: Well, I bet they have the phones
tapped. I always said that. It's the phones.

991
01:00:14,722 --> 01:00:17,486
WILSON: I can't believe they would
pull this shit on Dwayne Andreas.

992
01:00:17,658 --> 01:00:19,592
MARK: Look, I get phone calls
from time to time.

993
01:00:19,761 --> 01:00:21,353
WILSON:
I know, I know.

994
01:00:22,030 --> 01:00:23,224
Oh, God.

995
01:00:23,398 --> 01:00:25,764
We're going to the lawyers.
I don't want phones.

996
01:00:25,933 --> 01:00:27,093
See? The phones.

997
01:00:27,268 --> 01:00:29,600
They hit everybody.
My dad, Schmidt, Randall.

998
01:00:29,771 --> 01:00:30,795
Oh, fuck me.

999
01:00:30,972 --> 01:00:33,167
No, they played me a tape of me.

1000
01:00:33,341 --> 01:00:36,401
Some meeting with the fucking Japanese.
I called the lawyers.

1001
01:00:36,577 --> 01:00:38,841
- We're gonna go there.
- Yeah? They played a tape.

1002
01:00:39,013 --> 01:00:42,642
- How the fuck did they get a tape?
- I really don't think they have that much.

1003
01:00:42,817 --> 01:00:45,217
When you factor in everything
we've done for them...

1004
01:00:45,386 --> 01:00:48,514
...this will be a 10-year thing
for the lawyers. Maybe a fine.

1005
01:00:48,689 --> 01:00:52,420
That's all this is ever gonna be.
Trust me.

1006
01:00:52,627 --> 01:00:53,958
[DOOR CLOSES]

1007
01:00:54,495 --> 01:00:55,587
- How's it going?
- Good.

1008
01:00:55,763 --> 01:00:57,526
FBI.

1009
01:00:58,466 --> 01:01:02,425
Yeah, he's here.
I got Agent Temples for Attorney Mutchnik.

1010
01:01:05,473 --> 01:01:06,667
This is James Mutchnik.

1011
01:01:06,841 --> 01:01:09,207
TEMPLES: Just interviewed
an ADM employee, Kirk Schmidt.

1012
01:01:10,078 --> 01:01:14,310
Schmidt knew we were coming.
Says he knew about the raid days ago.

1013
01:01:15,416 --> 01:01:17,475
He says Whitacre told him.

1014
01:01:18,753 --> 01:01:19,879
Thanks.

1015
01:01:20,054 --> 01:01:23,455
- He sees you sitting in the window and...
- Bob. Brian.

1016
01:01:23,624 --> 01:01:25,353
Can I talk to you guys for a second?

1017
01:01:30,665 --> 01:01:33,065
That was amazing.
You guys should have seen it.

1018
01:01:33,234 --> 01:01:36,362
Oh, Terry was so scared,
and Mick and the lawyers, they were just...

1019
01:01:36,537 --> 01:01:38,266
- They were pissed.
SHEPARD: That's super.

1020
01:01:38,439 --> 01:01:40,805
They thought you guys
gave me the once-over.

1021
01:01:40,975 --> 01:01:43,307
They're like, "You all right?"
I'm going, "Yeah."

1022
01:01:43,478 --> 01:01:46,572
- Did you make a tape?
- Yeah, I made a tape. A great one.

1023
01:01:46,747 --> 01:01:48,009
Really good.

1024
01:01:48,182 --> 01:01:49,979
So it's over, then.

1025
01:01:50,151 --> 01:01:51,175
SHEPARD:
Mark...

1026
01:01:52,353 --> 01:01:53,650
...who did you tell?

1027
01:01:55,022 --> 01:01:58,856
- What?
- Who else did you tell about the raid?

1028
01:02:03,464 --> 01:02:05,091
Well...

1029
01:02:06,200 --> 01:02:07,861
I had to tell my secretary.

1030
01:02:09,036 --> 01:02:12,699
Guys, I'm the head
of the bioproducts division.

1031
01:02:12,874 --> 01:02:16,207
She has to know where to get in touch
with me. I told her months ago.

1032
01:02:16,377 --> 01:02:19,938
So all I said was,
"Liz, I'm doing some work with the FBI.

1033
01:02:20,114 --> 01:02:22,139
I might be out of touch for a while."

1034
01:02:22,316 --> 01:02:26,616
That's it.
She had no idea about our case.

1035
01:02:32,827 --> 01:02:36,285
I'm pretty sure I've mentioned the name
Kathy Dougherty a time or two...

1036
01:02:36,464 --> 01:02:37,761
...in my division.

1037
01:02:37,932 --> 01:02:43,427
Kathy is a friend. She is a trusted ally.

1038
01:02:43,604 --> 01:02:45,071
I didn't want her to be scared.

1039
01:02:45,239 --> 01:02:48,106
Why would you do that, Mark?
Why would you tell Dougherty?

1040
01:02:48,276 --> 01:02:53,111
Because I didn't want her to be scared.
I trust her.

1041
01:02:53,281 --> 01:02:55,715
- Guys, we can trust Kathy.
- Who else?

1042
01:02:55,883 --> 01:02:58,044
Don't jack us around, Mark.

1043
01:03:01,822 --> 01:03:03,449
Mm.

1044
01:03:03,758 --> 01:03:06,886
Kirk Schmidt. I mean, Schmidty...

1045
01:03:07,061 --> 01:03:10,258
Look, I was afraid that he wouldn't
say anything to you guys.

1046
01:03:10,431 --> 01:03:12,865
That he'd clam up on account
of he's loyal to me.

1047
01:03:13,034 --> 01:03:15,502
You could have ruined
this entire operation.

1048
01:03:15,670 --> 01:03:17,934
Has anything gone wrong?
Has anything gone wrong?

1049
01:03:18,105 --> 01:03:19,572
Time out. Time out. Time out.

1050
01:03:21,209 --> 01:03:25,578
Mark, you know what you did,
in our eyes, was wrong.

1051
01:03:26,781 --> 01:03:31,150
- It was supposed to be a secret.
SHEPARD: Look, we can get past this.

1052
01:03:31,319 --> 01:03:35,221
But is there anything else
that we need to know?

1053
01:03:35,389 --> 01:03:37,016
No.

1054
01:03:37,892 --> 01:03:39,484
No, not that I can think of.

1055
01:03:46,133 --> 01:03:47,862
Remember...

1056
01:03:48,035 --> 01:03:50,026
...tell them you're getting
your own lawyer.

1057
01:03:50,204 --> 01:03:53,196
MARK:
I know about the lawyers, Brian!

1058
01:04:39,020 --> 01:04:41,921
Mark Whitacre, Aubrey Daniel.

1059
01:04:42,089 --> 01:04:44,683
Pleasure to meet you.
I'm representing ADM in this matter.

1060
01:04:44,859 --> 01:04:45,917
Okay.

1061
01:04:46,093 --> 01:04:49,187
- This is John Dowd, a colleague of mine.
- Good morning, John.

1062
01:04:49,363 --> 01:04:52,958
Dwayne has filled us in
on your responsibilities here, so...

1063
01:04:53,200 --> 01:04:57,034
Aubrey prosecuted Lieutenant Calley
after the My Lai massacre in Vietnam...

1064
01:04:57,204 --> 01:05:00,662
...so this ought to be a cakewalk
for him.

1065
01:05:00,841 --> 01:05:03,105
We were hoping you'd have time
to talk to John.

1066
01:05:03,277 --> 01:05:05,745
- Sure.
- ADM's behind you on this, Mark.

1067
01:05:05,913 --> 01:05:08,609
Dad and I want all the key people
to know...

1068
01:05:08,783 --> 01:05:11,115
...that we're gonna be paying
all your legal fees.

1069
01:05:11,285 --> 01:05:13,776
Oh, great. Great.
Thank you, that's great.

1070
01:05:13,954 --> 01:05:17,412
Then... Then we'll let you fellas
get acquainted, okay?

1071
01:05:17,591 --> 01:05:18,683
Okay.

1072
01:05:20,928 --> 01:05:24,364
- How you holding up, Mark? Thanks.
- Good. Please, sit down.

1073
01:05:25,299 --> 01:05:26,732
[SIGHS]

1074
01:05:29,337 --> 01:05:32,238
- John, can I ask you something?
- Sure, anything.

1075
01:05:32,406 --> 01:05:36,809
If I say something to you, are you allowed
to say anything to Mick and Dwayne?

1076
01:05:40,715 --> 01:05:42,706
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1077
01:05:55,129 --> 01:05:57,120
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

1078
01:06:04,772 --> 01:06:06,672
Oh. Here we go.

1079
01:06:17,118 --> 01:06:21,350
MARK: I need to tell you I'm gonna
be cooperating with the FBI.

1080
01:06:21,889 --> 01:06:23,447
They have hundreds of tapes.

1081
01:06:24,625 --> 01:06:26,616
They know all about lysine.

1082
01:06:27,728 --> 01:06:30,663
And John here agrees with me
I should be getting another lawyer.

1083
01:06:30,831 --> 01:06:33,459
Oh. No question about it.

1084
01:06:36,804 --> 01:06:39,170
I want to say sorry
for everything that's happened.

1085
01:06:39,340 --> 01:06:40,637
Sorry?

1086
01:06:41,876 --> 01:06:43,434
What's that?

1087
01:06:44,311 --> 01:06:46,643
It feels good to talk, to clear the air.

1088
01:06:46,814 --> 01:06:48,873
You get to be like a balloon
after a while...

1089
01:06:49,049 --> 01:06:52,883
...a balloon looking for a pin
to bump into and relieve the pressure.

1090
01:06:53,053 --> 01:06:56,489
You could get sick from keeping it inside
and get a tumor or something.

1091
01:06:56,657 --> 01:06:58,022
I didn't ask for that.

1092
01:06:58,459 --> 01:07:00,950
I have a friend from school
who has a law practice.

1093
01:07:01,128 --> 01:07:04,291
And he's always telling me
how they can't talk about their cases.

1094
01:07:04,465 --> 01:07:06,831
Like in The Firm.
You can tell them anything.

1095
01:07:07,001 --> 01:07:11,165
They have to keep it to themselves or they
get in a lot of trouble. They're boxed.

1096
01:07:11,338 --> 01:07:13,329
That's what they say: Boxed.

1097
01:07:13,707 --> 01:07:16,608
LAWYER: So there wasn't a saboteur
at all. You made that up?

1098
01:07:16,777 --> 01:07:19,610
MARK: Well, maybe there was.
I mean, there could have been.

1099
01:07:19,780 --> 01:07:21,077
Okay.

1100
01:07:21,248 --> 01:07:23,148
ADM steals technology
from the Japanese...

1101
01:07:23,317 --> 01:07:26,548
...so I wouldn't put it past the Japanese
to do the same thing to us.

1102
01:07:26,720 --> 01:07:29,245
But once I told the FBI
that I'd made that part up...

1103
01:07:29,423 --> 01:07:33,757
...they said I had very little choice
but to be a cooperating witness.

1104
01:07:34,428 --> 01:07:37,920
And you began making tapes.
How many tapes did you make?

1105
01:07:38,098 --> 01:07:41,158
There are over 200 tapes.

1106
01:07:41,569 --> 01:07:43,230
Ooh.

1107
01:07:43,604 --> 01:07:47,665
There are so many really nice people
in the world, people who want to help out.

1108
01:07:47,842 --> 01:07:49,935
Good neighbors, good listeners.

1109
01:07:50,211 --> 01:07:52,179
Like when they had floods
in Mississippi...

1110
01:07:52,346 --> 01:07:55,008
...and people lose everything
and are sleeping in a gym...

1111
01:07:55,182 --> 01:07:59,482
...someone always shows up with a warm
coat and a homemade pot roast.

1112
01:07:59,653 --> 01:08:04,147
That's why Ginger and I bought that girl
a computer after she had the spine injury.

1113
01:08:04,325 --> 01:08:06,725
That kind of thing
really makes a difference.

1114
01:08:06,894 --> 01:08:08,759
Jim here strikes me as that kind of guy.

1115
01:08:08,929 --> 01:08:12,387
He's the one-in-a-hundred guy who, when
you come into the emergency room...

1116
01:08:12,566 --> 01:08:14,659
...you thank your lucky stars
it's his watch.

1117
01:08:14,835 --> 01:08:18,202
- Illegal campaign contributions,
whatever. Whatever we're talking about.

1118
01:08:18,372 --> 01:08:20,772
So then I'd come back.
Two nights a week or so...

1119
01:08:20,941 --> 01:08:23,910
...Brian and Bob and I
would get together, and we'd...

1120
01:08:24,078 --> 01:08:27,445
You know, we'd work it.
We'd build the investigation.

1121
01:08:27,615 --> 01:08:30,049
Get everything we needed,
gather all the information.

1122
01:08:30,217 --> 01:08:32,276
Then we went to DOJ,
briefed those lawyers...

1123
01:08:32,453 --> 01:08:36,253
...and before you knew it, we were hitting
ADM, raiding the place, taking it down.

1124
01:08:36,423 --> 01:08:38,857
And for how long did you do this?
Work as an informant?

1125
01:08:39,026 --> 01:08:42,484
Ahh, ooh. Two and a half years.

1126
01:08:43,330 --> 01:08:46,766
Two and a half years.

1127
01:08:46,934 --> 01:08:48,629
You know, and I always thought...

1128
01:08:48,802 --> 01:08:52,169
...there'd still be a place for me at ADM
when this whole thing was over.

1129
01:08:52,339 --> 01:08:54,534
I still have a lot of friends there.

1130
01:08:54,708 --> 01:08:55,732
A lot of friends.

1131
01:08:58,846 --> 01:09:00,507
Hey, Mark...

1132
01:09:01,115 --> 01:09:04,915
...it's very important to your case you
not discuss this with anyone else. Okay?

1133
01:09:05,519 --> 01:09:10,081
These people you work with, your friends,
they could end up being witnesses.

1134
01:09:10,257 --> 01:09:14,125
Bob and I are the only people
you talk to about this from now on.

1135
01:09:14,461 --> 01:09:17,589
All right? And I want you to know
that you can tell us anything.

1136
01:09:18,799 --> 01:09:20,289
- Okay. Yeah.
EPSTEIN: Okay?

1137
01:09:20,467 --> 01:09:24,631
Well, they kept coming to the house
and they only had ADM's side of the story.

1138
01:09:24,872 --> 01:09:27,397
SHEPARD [OVER PHONE]: Did you
talk to The Wall Street Journal, Mark?

1139
01:09:27,575 --> 01:09:30,874
What did you say? It's real important
that you not talk to the press.

1140
01:09:31,145 --> 01:09:34,308
Me? I told them I had no comment,
but it didn't matter.

1141
01:09:34,481 --> 01:09:37,541
They had the story anyway.
They already had it.

1142
01:09:39,186 --> 01:09:42,644
Did you see my stipple portrait?
It's pretty good.

1143
01:09:48,796 --> 01:09:50,525
EPSTEIN:
Oh, shit.

1144
01:09:57,338 --> 01:10:00,865
MAN 1: I'd appreciate any comment you
can make on the allegations on the TV.

1145
01:10:01,041 --> 01:10:03,373
Just a quick comment.
What do you have to say?

1146
01:10:03,544 --> 01:10:08,641
I came out to tell you that I'm not allowed
to talk to the press at this time.

1147
01:10:08,816 --> 01:10:11,250
WOMAN: At least any comment
on the effects of your actions...

1148
01:10:11,418 --> 01:10:13,249
...on ADM's declining stock prices?

1149
01:10:13,420 --> 01:10:16,548
What's been the reaction
of your friends being taped?

1150
01:10:16,724 --> 01:10:19,852
Well, I'm a person of interest in an
ongoing investigation.

1151
01:10:20,027 --> 01:10:22,689
MAN 2: Do you believe you and your
family can stay in Decatur?

1152
01:10:22,863 --> 01:10:24,694
Has the government made arrangements
to move you?

1153
01:10:24,865 --> 01:10:26,059
[REPORTERS CLAMORING]

1154
01:10:28,769 --> 01:10:31,602
We're still getting
the threatening phone calls.

1155
01:10:31,939 --> 01:10:34,874
And I know for a fact
that Dwayne and Terry...

1156
01:10:35,042 --> 01:10:39,945
...have been telling people that he wasn't
a good worker and he can't be trusted.

1157
01:10:40,114 --> 01:10:41,945
We told Mark.

1158
01:10:42,216 --> 01:10:44,707
We told him
that he had to expect the unexpected...

1159
01:10:44,885 --> 01:10:46,352
...that he might be attacked...

1160
01:10:46,520 --> 01:10:50,217
...that he wasn't gonna win
any popularity contests for this.

1161
01:10:50,391 --> 01:10:53,451
Well, he just mopes around here
all day...

1162
01:10:53,627 --> 01:10:57,028
...watching the news,
looking for a glimpse of himself.

1163
01:10:57,197 --> 01:11:02,294
Or he's calling someone from ADM,
trying to get the latest gossip.

1164
01:11:03,137 --> 01:11:07,574
Maybe you guys should get out of town
until the hearings start.

1165
01:11:07,808 --> 01:11:09,776
He's got to stop talking to people.

1166
01:11:13,881 --> 01:11:15,906
Well, the FBI never forced me
to cooperate.

1167
01:11:16,150 --> 01:11:17,879
I don't owe Brian Shepard the truth.

1168
