1631
01:40:11,850 --> 01:40:16,583
The idea to sue him
came from someone inside ADM.

1632
01:40:16,755 --> 01:40:19,519
I shouldn't have listened.
I don't even remember who it was.

1633
01:40:20,492 --> 01:40:25,520
While I was there at ADM, I lived so many
lives, I didn't really know who I was.

1634
01:40:26,265 --> 01:40:31,202
And I know today more who I am
and what I really want out of life.

1635
01:40:31,370 --> 01:40:36,467
I've completed three postgraduate
degrees while in detention...

1636
01:40:36,642 --> 01:40:39,509
...a J.D., which is, of course,
a law degree...

1637
01:40:39,678 --> 01:40:42,909
...another advanced degree
in the psychology of jury selection.

1638
01:40:43,449 --> 01:40:46,748
I sleep better here in prison
than I have in years.

1639
01:40:46,919 --> 01:40:49,979
My wife, Ginger, has forgiven me.

1640
01:40:50,789 --> 01:40:53,280
She actually believes
that this incident with ADM...

1641
01:40:53,525 --> 01:40:57,552
...brought us closer together
in a marriage of over 20 years.

1642
01:40:57,996 --> 01:40:59,964
And I hope you'll allow me
to leave here...

1643
01:41:00,132 --> 01:41:03,829
...so that I can rejoin that life
with my family, my three kids...

1644
01:41:04,002 --> 01:41:05,367
...two of whom are adopted.

1645
01:41:05,871 --> 01:41:09,830
Especially in light of the fact that
in large part because of my testimony...

1646
01:41:10,008 --> 01:41:13,136
...the United States government
has to date been able to collect...

1647
01:41:13,312 --> 01:41:17,271
...over one billion dollars in price-fixing
fines from big businesses.

1648
01:41:18,050 --> 01:41:20,883
So that's it. Thanks.

1649
01:41:31,797 --> 01:41:33,560
Good luck with the pardon, Mark.

1650
01:41:33,732 --> 01:41:37,224
Thanks, Bob. Thanks for helping me
remember everything.

1651
01:41:37,402 --> 01:41:39,336
I wish Brian could have come.

1652
01:41:39,571 --> 01:41:43,337
- Well, he's still pretty angry.
- Yeah.

1653
01:41:43,509 --> 01:41:46,842
Well, tell him I'm real sorry.
Will you do that?

1654
01:41:47,012 --> 01:41:48,274
Sure, Mark.

1655
01:41:48,447 --> 01:41:50,813
The irony is
if I hadn't gone undercover...

1656
01:41:50,983 --> 01:41:54,578
...I never would have stole the 11
and a half million. It was my way out.

1657
01:41:54,753 --> 01:41:58,086
It was my severance. What else
was I gonna do? I had to write my own.

1658
01:41:58,257 --> 01:41:59,747
MAN:
Work detail.

1659
01:42:00,425 --> 01:42:01,756
See you, Bob.

1660
01:42:02,027 --> 01:42:04,825
- Uh-uh... Uh-uh... Eleven and a half million?
- What?

1661
01:42:04,997 --> 01:42:06,897
I thought it was nine and a half.

1662
01:42:07,065 --> 01:42:09,829
- What did I say?
- You said 11 and a half.

1663
01:42:10,002 --> 01:42:13,802
You do know that the people at ADM
think you were the mole.

1664
01:42:13,972 --> 01:42:17,373
That you planted the virus,
then made it go away.

1665
01:42:17,609 --> 01:42:20,510
The 11 and a half
is with the interest.

1666
01:42:21,446 --> 01:42:24,438
Mark, is it nine and a half
or 11 and a half?

1667
01:42:24,616 --> 01:42:25,640
[MARK SIGHS]

1668
01:42:25,817 --> 01:42:27,546
I don't know, Bob.

1669
01:42:28,620 --> 01:42:29,848
You tell me.

1670
01:42:40,966 --> 01:42:42,365
[DOOR CLOSES]

1671
